tr.td: Newfoundland and Labrador / Terre-Neuve-et-Labrador

Low probabilities dominate the island of Newfoundland, with moderate increases along the northern peninsula. Labrador has generally moderate probability, ranging to high in northern North Coast region.
Prince Edward Island / Île-du-Prince-Édouard
Moderate probabilities dominate across the province.
Nova Scotia / Nouvelle-Écosse
Low probabilities dominate, with slight increases in the Cape Breton highlands.
New Brunswick / Nouveau-Brunswick
Low to moderate probabilities dominate across the province, with moderate values in the central and northwest towards the Gaspé.
Quebec / Québec
Northern Quebec shows higher probabilities, with moderate to low values in central and southern regions.
Ontario
Northern regions exhibit moderate probabilities, transitioning to generally low in southern areas, with some moderate increase north of Lake Superior.
Manitoba
Low probabilities dominate the province, with moderate to increases in northwestern regions.
Saskatchewan
Low probabilities dominate in southern and central regions, with moderate values in the northeast.
Alberta
Low probabilities dominate, with moderate values near the southwestern mountain region.
British Columbia / Colombie-Britannique
Moderate to high probabilities dominate the coastal and mountainous regions, with lower values in the interior.
Yukon
Low probabilities are found the interior, with moderate to high probabilities in mountainous and coastal regions.
Northwest Territories / Territoires du Nord-Ouest
Very low probabilities dominate in the south, with moderate to high probability in the great lakes and coastal regions.
Nunavut
Moderate probabilities towards the southern borders, with high values in Hudson's Bay, the Arctic archipelago and most coastal regions. Permanent snow and ice can be found in the northern islands.
